The paper deals with physical layer security in wireless networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses jamming techniques to protect against eavesdropping, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of relay nodes and power allocation also involves optimization and control theory (cs.SY) and signal processing (cs.MM).
